(15, 2, 'Female polite particle', 'ค่ะ', 'Khâ', '', 'Particle used by female speakers at the end of a sentence for politeness, as a response when their name is called, and during a conversation to indicate agreement. Pronounced with different tones depending on the context. Thai has many particles which have no equivalent in English. They are generally used to indicate politeness or imply a question.', 'f2_1'),
