(243, 9, '6am', 'หกโมงเช้า', 'Hòhk mohng cháao', 'six - hour - morning', 'From 6AM to 11AM, use the hour followed by “mohng cháao”. ', 'f9_37'),
(244, 9, '7am', 'เจ็ดโมงเช้า / หนึ่งโมงเช้า', 'Jèt mohng cháao / Nèung mohng cháao', 'seven - hour - morning / one - hour - morning', 'From 7AM to 11AM, some people count 7AM as 1, 8AM as 2 and so on. This comes from the tradition of the temples sounding a drum once at 7AM, twice at 8AM etc.', 'f9_38'),
(245, 9, '8am', 'แปดโมงเช้า / สองโมงเช้า ', 'Bpàet mohng cháao / Săawng mohng cháao', 'eight - hour - morning / two - hour - morning', '', 'f9_39'),
(246, 9, '10:15am', 'สิบโมงสิบห้า / สี่โมงสิบห้า', 'Sìp mohng sìp-hâa  / Sìi mohng sìp-hâa', 'ten - hour  - fifteen / four - hour - fifteen', 'You do not say ''cháao'' when including minutes past the hour.', 'f9_40'),
