(250, 9, '2pm', 'บ่ายสองโมง', 'Bàai săawng mohng', 'afternoon - two - hours', 'From 1PM to 4PM, use the word “bàai” followed by the hour, then “mohng”.', 'f9_44'),
(251, 9, '4pm', 'สี่โมงเย็น / บ่ายสี่โมง', 'Sìi mohng yen / Bàai sìi mohng', 'four - hour - early evening / afternoon - four - hour', 'Late afternoon / early evening is known as ''yen''. 4PM may be ''bàai'' or ''yen''.', 'f9_45'),
(252, 9, '5:15pm', 'ห้าโมงสิบห้า', 'Hâa mohng sìp-hâa', 'five - hour - fifteen', 'For 5PM and 6PM use the hour followed by ''mohng yen''. If there are mintues you can omit ''yen''.', 'f9_46'),
(253, 9, '7pm', 'หนึ่งทุ่ม / ทุ่มหนึ่ง ', 'Nèung thûm / Thûm nèung', 'one - evening / evening - one', 'ทุ่ม (Thûm) means ''evening''. The evening hours follow a similar convention to the morning, with 7PM being 1, 8PM being 2 and so on until 11PM. However, unlike the morning there tends to be just this one system.', 'f9_47'),
(254, 9, '7:30pm', 'ทุ่มครึ่ง / หนึ่งทุ่มครึ่ง', 'Thûm khrêung / Nèung thûm khrêung', 'evening - half / one - evening - half', '', 'f9_48'),
