(271, 10, 'It', 'มัน', 'Mun', '', 'Used for animals as well as objects.', 'f10_11'),
(272, 10, 'Please give it to Mr Komgrit.', 'ช่วยเอามาให้คุณคมกริต', 'Chûay ao maa hâi khun Komgrit ', 'help - take to - give - title of respect - Komgrit', 'The words ''ao maa'' together mean ''take to''.', 'f10_12'),
(273, 10, 'Teacher, I have finished.', 'คุณครู เสร็จแล้วค่ะ', 'Khun khruu, sèt láew khâ.', 'title of respect - teacher - finish -  past tense marker - polite particle', 'It is common to omit pronouns if the context makes it obvious.', 'f10_13'),
